data.description: Tucked away on a tree-lined street in Austin’s Colorado Crossing neighborhood this charming  corner-lot house immediately feels like home. Step inside to find an open floor plan suitable for entertaining, where golden morning light filters into the kitchen & combined dining space inviting homemade breakfasts before busy workday mornings. One of four bedrooms is on this main level along with a full bathroom, perfect for an in-law or overnight guest scenario. On the second level you’ll discover an expansive open loft space that meanders into the remaining bedrooms, all tucked away from each other. The primary bedroom features an en-suite bathroom that expands into a massive walk-in closet for all your storage wants and needs. Utilize the additional bedrooms for vacationers or creating an in-home office/gaming space.   Throughout the yard plants and planters have been updated to bring in fresh and bright foliage.   Out back a newly laid crushed granite sitting area includes a spot for a fire pit, to leisure in the cool Texas evenings. Trees in the corner of the lot provide ample shade when things do heat back up. Parks, golf courses, and walking/hiking trails are prevalent and within short proximity to the home. You won’t have to travel far to take a trip out of town at the Austin-Bergstrom Airport. The essences of downtown Austin nightlife is also very short ride away with.  With its welcoming natural light and numerous contemporary updates, this home embodies an effortlessly fresh and open spirit that attracts modern Austin dwellers.
